org.js4ms.service.protocol.rest.message
Class MessageHeaderParser

java.lang.Object
  org.js4ms.service.protocol.rest.message.MessageHeaderParser

public class MessageHeaderParser
extends Object

Maintains a map of MessageHeaderFactory objects and uses those factories to construct MessageHeader objects from a raw message header record or a specified name and value.

construct

public MessageHeader construct(String name,
                               String value)
                        throws IllegalArgumentException
Constructs a concrete MessageHeader object from a given name and value. This methods uses the specified name to lookup a message header factory, and if one exists, uses that factory to construct a MessageHeader object from the specified value. If no factory has been registered for the specified name, this method will return a SimpleMessageHeader constructed using the name and value arguments.

Parameters:
name - - The header name used to lookup a factory.
value - - The header value.
Returns:
A MessageHeader object.
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - If the specified value cannot be used to construct a message header of the type identified by the name.
